Consider the function

\begin{align*}
F(x) = \begin{cases}
a & \text{if } x < 0, \\
k \arctan x & \text{if } 0 \leq x \leq 1, \\
b & \text{if } x \geq 1.
\end{cases}
\end{align*}

\textbf{(b)} Let \emph{X} be the continuous random variable with
cummulative distribution function \emph{F(x)} as given in part
{(a)}.
Find the probability density function of \emph{X}.
